title: Millburn High School varsity girls tennis team claims 10th straight section title
text:
Millburn High School varsity girls tennis team claims 10th straight section title October 15, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 15, 2015, 10:53 AM By Jim Connelly Buy this photo photo courtesy of rick gray Elizabeth Gray has the honor of holding the championship plaque Oct. 13 following the Millburn High School varsity girls tennis team's 3-2 defeat of West Windsor-Plainsboro South High School in the New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association North Jersey, Section 2, Group 3 final. Sitting, from left, are Alex Pritsker, Sara Jacobs, Gray, Jessica Raystin, Macey Wardius and Ishika Gupta. Standing, from left, are head coach Bill Wickenheisser, Isabella Waung, Joanna Atwater, Sydney Zirlin, Anna Mandel, Paige Sollender, Stephanie Schrage and assistant coach Lee Robinson. 
A 10th consecutive state sectional tournament championship did not come easily for Millburn High School's varsity girls tennis team. 
The top-seeded Millers, after building a quick 2-0 lead against second-seeded West Windsor-Plainsboro South High School Oct. 13 in the New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association North Jersey, Section 2, Group 3 final at the Garden State Tennis Center in Edison, posted a 3-2 victory. Buy this photo photo courtesy of rick gray The celebration is on for the Millburn High School varsity girls tennis team after the first doubles team of Isabella Waung and Sydney Zirlin provided the clinching point in the sectional final against West Windsor-Plainsboro South High School. 
Millburn's first doubles team of Sydney Zirlin and Isabella Waung recorded a victory in three sets, clinching the victory at 3-1. 
"Wow," exclaimed Miller head coach Bill Wickenheisser the morning after the match. 
"This was one of the best matches I have ever been involved in and it was a doozy of a sectional final." 
Millburn's first points were provided by Stephanie Schrage at first singles and the second doubles team of Elizabeth Gray and Anna Mandel. 
Schrage cruised to a 6-1, 6-0 defeat of Claudia Siniakowicz. 
Gray and Mandel's 6-0, 6-4 defeat of Michelle Wong and Manogna Konduri left Millburn needing to win one of the final three matches to gain a berth in the Group 3 semifinals. 
West Windsor-Plainboro South's Caroline Zhou shaved Millburn's advantage to 2-1 with a 6-4, 5-7 defeat of Joanna Atwater at third singles. 
Close to an hour following the conclusion of the third singles match, Zirlin and Waung ended the suspense with a 6-4, 4-6, 6-3 defeat of Kimberly Wong and Stephanie Ji. 
"I am so proud of the girls," Wickenheisser said. "With only two returning starters (Schrage and Zirlin) this was a huge accomplishment for us. This will give us a lot of confidence." 
The second singles match, with the team outcome decided, went to a super tiebreaker in the third set. 
West Windsor-Plainsboro South's Angela Weng outlasted Alex Pritsker 6-7 (6-8), 7-6 (8-6), 10-4. 
"We were able to take care of business and now we get ready for the next step," Wickenheisser said. 
The next step is a meeting with North Jersey, Section 1 winner Northern Highlands Regional High School today, Oct. 15, in the Group 3 semifinals at 9 a.m. at Mercer County Park. 
Central Jersey champion Moorestown High School opposes South Jersey champion Mainland Regional High School in the other 9 a.m. semifinal. 
The semifinal winners return at 1 p.m. to vie for a berth in next week's NJSIAA Tournament of Champions.
